quran[9]{c,v,t}:
  42,23,"That is that whereof Allah giveth the glad tidings Unto His bondmen who believe and work righteous works, Say thou: I ask of you no hire therefor save affection in respect of kinship. And whoso ever earneth a good deed We shall increase Unto him good in respect thereof; verily Allah is Forgiving, Appreciative"
  42,24,"Say they: he hath fabricated a lie concerning God! Now, if Allah willed, He would seal thine heart. And Allah abolisheth falsehood and establisheth truth by His words; verily He is the Knower of that which is in the breasts"
  42,25,"And He it is Who accepteth repentances from His bondmen, and pardoneth the evil deeds and knoweth that which ye do"
  42,26,And He answereth those who believe and work righteous works and increaseth Unto them of His grace. And the infidels! theirs shall be a severe torment
  42,27,"And had Allah expanded the provision for His bondmen they surely would have rebelled in the earth, but He sendeth down by measure as He willeth; verily He is, in respect of His bondmen. Aware and Beholder"
  42,28,"And He it is Who sendeth down the rain after men have despaired, and spreadeth abroad His mercy. And He is the Patron of all, the Praiseworthy"
  42,29,And of His signs is the creation of the heavens and the earth and of the moving creatures which He hath dispersed in the twain. And He is for their assembling whensoever He will Potent
  42,30,And whatsoever of affliction befalleth you is owing to that which your hands have earned; and He pardoneth much
  42,31,And ye cannot frustrate His Punishment in the earth; and there is for you beside Allah neither protector nor helper